{
  "stem": "9963.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I couldn't go no place anymore.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had to wear a-- imagine from the walking-- I had my feet swollen until it was infected, but I couldn't hardly walk.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But my brother right away left.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then my other brother left.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they went to the Russian sector.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Me, they right away, the Germans, took me to work in the city-- even I was sick, but they didn't care.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They told me that I had to chop wood for the German soldiers over there for the kitchen to cook, or to sweep all the streets and things like this-- all kind of work in the city what I had to work every day for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was right in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Later, about a month later, or maybe more than this, the first snow fall down was a very heavy snow-- was a couple feet of snow.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So the train couldn't go through.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So they took us, all Jewish people from the city, to clean all the-- the train-- the-- the-- dig where the train goes.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We-- we start, and I remember that's Thursday to-- to sweep it and to clean the-- over there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "When we finished, let's say, a couple kilometers, but the snow was so fast that we had to go back and start from the beginning.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So the-- the-- the job was Thursday-- Thursday day, Thursday night, Friday a whole day.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Friday afternoon, when the-- the snow stopped, this-- they let us home.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And they let us home, I went right away to bed to the-- to sleep.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Sure enough, in the evening, they knocked on the door, and they took me out again to clean the snow.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because it start snowing again.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
